Shiny web apps
========================================================

[Shiny](https://shiny.rstudio.com/) is an R package that makes it easy to build interactive web apps straight from R. You can host standalone apps on a webpage or embed them in R Markdown documents or build dashboards. Examples can be seen at [Shiny Gallary](https://shiny.rstudio.com/gallery/) or the [Showcase](https://www.rstudio.com/products/shiny/shiny-user-showcase/) gallery. Some examples are:

- [Distributions](https://gallery.shinyapps.io/dist_calc/)
- [Emergency Department Simulation](https://gallery.shinyapps.io/EDsimulation/)

***

- [Traveling Salesman](https://gallery.shinyapps.io/shiny-salesman/)
- [Central Limit Theorem for Means](https://gallery.shinyapps.io/CLT_mean/)
- [Bullwhip game](https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/bullwhipgame/index.html) (see below)

```{r, eval=FALSE}
library(bullwhipgame)
bullwhipgame()
```



